The paper deals with the formal synthesis of controllers for reactive systems, which is a topic in the field of control theory and systems engineering. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses game-solving algorithms, which are commonly used in the field of game theory, suggesting that cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is another likely category. The paper also introduces a modeling formalism and a synthesis algorithm, which are related to the field of logic and verification, making cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) a possible category. The paper also discusses the use of assume-admissible winning strategies, which are related to the field of artificial intelligence, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the construction of a dynamic controller, which involves programming and software engineering concepts, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) a possible category as well.
